The facility has also implemented the following administrative controls that reduce the probability of an EO or PO release:
?Routine inspections of storage tanks, rail cars, tank trucks and safety equipment;
?EO and PO storage tanks are only connected to other containers during transfer operations to reduce the risk of leaks; they are securely closed at all other times;
?Access to the EO and PO processes is restricted to specially trained operators who are issued keys required to transfer these materials;
?Storage tanks are partially bunkered and protected by a secondary containment wall;
?A nitrogen blanket is maintained in the storage tanks to inert the vapor in the tanks.

4. Five-year accident History

LTC has not had a reportable release within the past 5 years.

5. Emergency Response Program

LTC has worked and continues to work in cooperation with the Skokie Fire Department and the Villages of Skokie and Lincolnwood, IL to integrate the facility-specific emergency response plan into the community emergency response plan.  The cooperative effort started soon after the facility was acquired by Petroferm in 1998.

LTC?s emergency response plan assigns specific responsibilities to its staff to:
?Provide critical information to emergency responders;
?Notify local agencies of any emergency; and
?Notify local authorities of the danger, if any, to areas surrounding the facility.


6.Planned changes to improve safety

Petroferm Inc. acquired the LTC facility in March 1998. Petroferm has already accomplished manyl facility improvements to reduce the risk of a chemical release, such as:
?Improved security;
?Better isolation of the EO handling system;
?Installation of a water deluge system for the EO railcar; and
?Redundant safety valves to prevent over pressurization of the EO rail car.
?Installation of a dedicated nitrogen system for the EO process;
?Installation of te

mperature sensors and alarms for the EO railcar and transfer pump;
?Modernization of the facility including the replacement of aging equipment;
?Gas detectors, for early leak detection, have been purchased and will be installed;                                                                   ?A meteorological station together with state-of-the-art gas dispersion modeling software has been installed.                                                                                                                                                                            Processes are routinely changed to improve safety as a result of employee safety programs which include  monthly training sessions ,observations and suggestion programs, incident investigations and corrective action programs, audits and inspection programs and preventative maintenance programs.                                                                                                                                                                            Additional security upgrades are being considered.
